37    /**
38    * Using the infrastructure provided by VariableReferencePass, identify
39    * variables that are used only once and in a way that is safe to move, and then
40    * inline them.
41    *
42    * This pass has two "modes." One mode only inlines variables declared as
43    * constants, for legacy compiler clients. The second mode inlines any
44    * variable that we can provably inline. Note that the second mode is a
45    * superset of the first mode. We only support the first mode for
46    * backwards-compatibility with compiler clients that don't want
47    * --inline_variables.
48    *
49    * The approach of this pass is similar to {@link CrossModuleCodeMotion}
50    *
51    * @author kushal@google.com (Kushal Dave)
52    * @author nicksantos@google.com (Nick Santos)
53    */
